# Suport Ideal — convenções

- Always respect the folder structure
- Always prioritize reusable components
- Never place business logic inside UI components
- Prefer composition over duplication
- Always use TypeScript with strict typing
- Follow clean code and scalability principles
- When creating new UI, think if it can be reused → if yes, create a component

## 1. Component Strategy

- ANY reusable UI must be a component inside /components
- Even simple elements should be abstracted if they could be reused in the future
- Follow separation of concerns strictly

## 2. Code Quality

- Use clean architecture principles
- Use absolute imports if possible
- Strong typing everywhere (no any)
- Create types/interfaces whenever needed
- Follow modern patterns (hooks, server/client separation when needed)

## 3. Folder Responsibilities

- components → reusable UI
- utils → pure functions/helpers
- configs → global configs (constants, env mapping, etc)
- lib → integrations, services, external logic

## IMPORTANT

- Do NOT add unnecessary complexity
- Do NOT over-engineer
- Keep it minimal but EXTREMELY well structured
- The goal is a strong foundation for scaling
- Not run build
- Not create tree git or new branchs
